#why
Now there is a lot that could be said about Sally Ride, but she must be the essence of Girl Power! She flew two missions to space, worked on the investigative committees for both the Challenger and Columbia accidents and she worked as a physics professor at San Diego University.
The Governator inducted her into the California Hall of Fame. When asked silly questions about her gender and the role as an astronauts, she replied that she only saw herself as one thing - an astronaut. 
Illustrating how important equality is by setting gender asside, as well as inspiring young people to pursue careers in science, technology and academia - not to mention she is a total badass person! This puts her on the list.
